      <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">"Motivating Your Students" seminar-workshop for Makati Aikido Club instructors and future instructors</span> </span></small><small><span style="font-family: Arial;"></span></small></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: white;">.</span></p><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">On
Friday, November 7th, Makati Aikido Club instructors and future
instructors are to undergo a training seminar-workshop on "Motivating
Your Students." By invitation. This is the first in a series of
off-the-mat training activities intended to professionalize the
teaching of Aikido in the Makati Aikido Club. The seminar will be
conducted by Royce Coffee, a trainor/instructor with more than 30 years
career experience in systems analysis and security. Participants shall
receive Certificates of Attendance.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Venue: Frazer Place, Valero St., Salcedo Village, Makati City.</span></small><br><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span></small><h3 style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400;"><i><span style="font-style: italic;">&nbsp;</span></i></span></font></h3>



      
      
      
      



      
      
      
